  "prompt": "Does Donald Trump believe in global warming?",
  "response": "Donald Trump's views on climate change have evolved over time. Throughout much of his presidency, he expressed skepticism about the scientific consensus on climate change and often referred to it as a \"hoax.\" His administration rolled back several environmental regulations and withdrew the U.S. from the Paris Agreement, which is an international accord aimed at combating climate change.\n\nHowever, in various interviews and statements, Trump has also acknowledged that the climate is changing and that human activity may play a role, but his focus has been more on economic considerations and energy independence rather than on climate action.\n\nAs of my last update in October 2023, Trump's stance on climate change may continue to influence his political rhetoric and actions. For the most current views or statements, it would be advisable to consult more recent sources.",
